<subSubSection id="CB67F5F96A22C502EFEA80DBE6081AB3" lastPageId="299" lastPageNumber="300" pageId="298" pageNumber="299" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="5B11B5EB877191B595BF952E70A682D5" pageId="298" pageNumber="299">
<taxonomicName id="DA3DB01F9043C5FFB6FE46E7F5810803" authorityName="Putzeys" authorityYear="1867" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dyschirius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="298" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melancholicus">Dyschirius melancholicus</taxonomicName>
Putzeys, 1867b: 41. Type locality: 
<normalizedToken id="78F858CC982BC0113EC46BAE2EE57A66" originalValue="«Daourie»">&quot;Daourie&quot;</normalizedToken>
(original citation). Holotype [by monotypy] probably in IRSN.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="75255F877BB7DA0B795918F41F5C0463" lastPageId="299" lastPageNumber="300" pageId="298" pageNumber="299">
<taxonomicName id="B4184065B17C9CCEE49AAFFF115EC4C6" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dyschirius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="298" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helleni">Dyschirius helleni</taxonomicName>
J. 
<normalizedToken id="B246562D3BE3DB5A0D82F06A95CC422D" originalValue="Müller">Mueller</normalizedToken>
, 1923: 78. Type locality: &quot;Dudinka [Taimyr Autonomous Okrug, Russia]&quot; (original citation). Lectotype, designated by Fedorenko (1996: 148), in MSNT. Synonymy established by Fedorenko (1990: 37). Etymology. The specific name was proposed for Wolter 
<normalizedToken id="5CE3D94D08FFA3214F5A14733F5E9E94" originalValue="Hellén">Hellen</normalizedToken>
[1890-1979], curator at the Zo 
<pageBreakToken id="5A1ED3027E514F6CF42F9FA1FE7DBE9F" pageId="299" pageNumber="300" start="start">ological</pageBreakToken>
Museum of the University of Helsinki, excellent collector, and specialist on parasitic 
<taxonomicName id="167EA950B2387BE5D16E9287476131F7" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Hymenoptera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Malvales" pageId="299" pageNumber="300" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Hymenoptera</taxonomicName>
of the Finnish fauna.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A0CC0241946A0FD8575772DCC8CE33EA" pageId="299" pageNumber="300">
<taxonomicName id="5B8744DF173AC58288E7BBC56705735A" authorityName="Munster" authorityYear="1923" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dyschirius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="299" pageNumber="300" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="norvegicus">Dyschirius norvegicus</taxonomicName>
Munster, 1923b: 249. Type locality: 
<normalizedToken id="CB999776C66289ECD8F66E6623049E84" originalValue="«Sørum">&quot;Sorum</normalizedToken>
i 
<normalizedToken id="6613A8629D7BDE0FAC2E0F1F6BC9A215" originalValue="Våge">Vage</normalizedToken>
(antagelig i Tromsdalen) ved 
<normalizedToken id="8AE06DD1C711201D83C3927E73A4CD73" originalValue="Tromsø">Tromso</normalizedToken>
og Gorzzejok i Karasjok&quot; (original citation), restricted to 
<normalizedToken id="03416AC215901AF1D64483C6BE3E0532" originalValue="«Sörum">&quot;Soerum</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken id="42469B3777119ACBB6DFDD9BEDD43AF2" originalValue="Vågå">Vaga</normalizedToken>
, Norway&quot; by Lindroth (1961a: 153). Syntype(s) [4 originally cited] location unknown (possibly in ZMUO). Synonymy established, under the name 
<taxonomicName id="158B563C68FD03680DBFC2CEC66AB7F6" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dyschirius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="299" pageNumber="300" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helleni">
<emphasis id="655924737C744E48F354C7B34CB7C6D7" italics="true" pageId="299" pageNumber="300">Dyschirius helleni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="3FA2D0DED51CBB2C4E2DCEDAD6EF2665" originalValue="Müller">Mueller</normalizedToken>
, by 
<normalizedToken id="5E5234B39B571B7C6EAA552757F28D00" originalValue="Hellén">Hellen</normalizedToken>
(1934: 52), confirmed by Fedorenko (1990: 37).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3C4E8887BCAE1AB48829E3E31D7ECD8D" pageId="299" pageNumber="300">
<taxonomicName id="23C8BA2D61AF7E6723CFB16658224B99" authorityName="Fall" authorityYear="1926" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dyschirius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="299" pageNumber="300" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="secretus">Dyschirius secretus</taxonomicName>
Fall, 1926a: 130. Type locality: &quot;Anchorage, Alaska&quot; (original citation). Holotype (♀) in MCZ [# 23854]. Synonymy established, under the name 
<taxonomicName id="8914CB31D6D412C3782EE7D412E65E7A" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dyschirius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="299" pageNumber="300" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helleni">
<emphasis id="3B2628CCACD8706D1F2A63974DEB7CB6" italics="true" pageId="299" pageNumber="300">Dyschirius helleni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="C3C2D159CB15362A67E0A5172641D98A" originalValue="Müller">Mueller</normalizedToken>
, by Lindroth (1954b: 122).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7F5BB4D38C08C7C0479FA4945549B70F" pageId="299" pageNumber="300" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8D8ECE578F8B1E634086E0B0EC2A2FEB" pageId="299" pageNumber="300">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DCFD0677F39FA7FDEF1B9BDE7FD20E7B" pageId="299" pageNumber="300">
This Holarctic species ranges from Scandinavia (Balkenohl 2003: 226) to the Hudson Bay in northeastern Manitoba (Garry 1993: 94, as 
<taxonomicName id="9DCE37243867F6C34EA59ACE8B7B83B9" authorityName="Motschulsky" authorityYear="1844" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dyschirius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="299" pageNumber="300" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigricornis">
<emphasis id="F45B7DC5787CA5DCAAB9B99AE69D891B" italics="true" pageId="299" pageNumber="300">Dyschirius nigricornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Fossil remnants, dated between 10,800 and 20,530 years B.P., have been unearthed in central North Dakota (Ashworth and Schwert 1992: 260), northeastern Iowa (Schwert 1992: 76; Woodman et al. 1996: 17), and southeastern Iowa (Baker et al. 1986: 96).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
