<paragraph id="B2EF0AA2D834021A4CEFB07BB5FB6209" pageId="299" pageNumber="300">
<emphasis id="32A2A206E7607F44BB555564A2355112" bold="true" pageId="299" pageNumber="300">CAN</emphasis>
: MB, NT, NU, YT 
<emphasis id="67B488746A197259BE2770EE3F271B92" bold="true" pageId="299" pageNumber="300">USA</emphasis>
: AK - 
<emphasis id="79B3B3082825045C60AAAB93A685C232" bold="true" pageId="299" pageNumber="300">Holarctic</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4056A84FE9C0AF41E4C19A908A324686" pageId="299" pageNumber="300" type="note">
<paragraph id="0BDEAC9DC875AAA76A0824D17ECB8899" pageId="299" pageNumber="300">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BF51D9683D901751A16988B13346CFC8" pageId="299" pageNumber="300">
This species has long been known under the name 
<taxonomicName id="40C6C6FD8F66E54C78562E1E9459F85F" authorityName="Motschulsky" authorityYear="1844" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dyschirius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="299" pageNumber="300" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigricornis">
<emphasis id="29DE09F92BB6E5B8DB7D075DE95426D1" italics="true" pageId="299" pageNumber="300">Dyschirius nigricornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Motschulsky, 1844 in the North American literature.
</paragraph>
